window.bookSummaryJSON = "They bound me to him with blood.<br>Before I even knew what love was.<br>I was ten when the ritual sealed us.<br>A sacred vow.<br>A whispered command.<br>Protect her as shadow, as blade, as brother.<br>But they didn’t ask me if I could survive her loss.<br><br>Now she’s gone—my vow buried with her.<br>And in her place stands the girl who shares her blood.<br>The one I was never meant to want.<br>The one they hunted through fire and silence and blood-soaked marble floors.<br><br><b>Elaria Fontanesi</b> walks into my world broken.<br>A daughter of betrayal.<br>A girl forged in grief.<br>She doesn’t know who I am.<br>Or what I did to protect the house that murdered hers.<br>But fate isn’t patient.<br>And history doesn’t stay buried.<br>We are bound again—by legacy, by duty, by a lie sealed in shadow.<br><br>She sees the scars I never let show.<br>And I feel the pull I swore I’d never answer again.<br>This isn’t devotion.<br>It’s obsession veiled in loyalty.<br>A love that should have died with her sister…<br>But refuses to stay buried.<br>He was meant to protect me.<br><br><b>Now he just might ruin me.<br>And God help me—I think I’d let him.</b>"; 
